<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Insider trading?</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If your brother-in-law is a senior acc=
ounting executive at a public company, and that public company is secretly =
in negotiations to be acquired at a premium, and your brother-in-law is wor=
king on the deal, and you <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.co=
m/click/26053246.265643/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9saXRpZ2F0aW9uL2NvbXBsYWl=
udHMvMjAyMC9jb21wMjQ5ODIucGRm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB5817ba04" itemprop=
=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0=
00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
talk to him=C2=A0regularly</a>=C2=A0while the deal is being negotiated, =E2=
=80=9Cincluding by phone, at [your] daughters=E2=80=99 basketball events, a=
nd at multiple family gatherings over the Christmas holidays,=E2=80=9D and =
after each time you talk to him you buy some short-dated out-of-the-money c=
all options on his company=E2=80=99s stock, and you call your son and tell=
=C2=A0<em>him=C2=A0</em>to buy call options on the company=E2=80=99s stock,=
 and you=C2=A0take out a loan on your car to buy even more call options on =
the company=E2=80=99s stock, and you make up 100% of the volume in those ca=
ll options on some of the days you trade, and then shortly after Christmas =
the company announces the merger and the stock shoots up and you (and your =
son) make a ton of money on your call options=C2=A0=E2=80=94=C2=A0is that i=
llegal insider trading?</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I don=E2=80=99t kno=
w! It has the main hallmarks of insider trading:</p><ol style=3D"list-style=
-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=09<li style=3D"margin=
-bottom: 5px;"><a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/260=
53246.265643/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMT=
gtMDgtMTIvdGhlLTEwLWxhd3Mtb2YtaW5zaWRlci10cmFkaW5nP2NtcGlkPUJCRDEyMTUyMV9NT=
05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJt=
PTIxMTIxNSZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB3e5ae67=
e" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;">Short-dated out-of-the-money call options</a> on a merger targ=
et, and</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Brothers-in-law. (=E2=80=
=9CThe brother-in-law=E2=80=99s role=E2=80=9D in American culture, <a href=
=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/26053246.265643/aHR0cHM6L=
y93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjAtMDUtMDgvb2lsLXByaWNl=
cy13ZXJlLWEtYmVhdXRpZnVsLW15c3Rlcnk_Y21waWQ9QkJEMTIxNTIxX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXR=
tX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjExMjE1JnV0bV=
9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB7c9598ac" itemprop=3D"S=
toryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000=
; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom=
-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">I onc=
e wrote</a>, =E2=80=9Cis to insider trade on his brother-in-law=E2=80=99s i=
nformation.=E2=80=9D)</li></ol><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But notice that=
, in my litany of suspicious events, I did not actually say =E2=80=9Cand yo=
ur brother-in-law told you about the merger negotiations.=E2=80=9D Sure he =
was working on the merger, and sure he kept seeing you at basketball events=
 etc., and sure each time you saw him you went out and bought call options.=
 But maybe you just talked about basketball! Maybe seeing him reminded you =
that his company existed, and you went off and did fundamental research and=
 traded without any inside information from him. Or maybe you saw him looki=
ng stressed, or happy, or he rushed in late to basketball practice, and you=
 thought =E2=80=9Chmm something might be cooking at his work=E2=80=9D and b=
ought options without a tip from him.[1]</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">St=
ill, given that list of suspicious signs, it=E2=80=99s a safe bet that the =
Securities and Exchange Commission will bring an insider trading case. And =
in fact it did: This is a real case, the person who traded is Christopher C=
lark (who made $243,000 of profits; his son made $53,000), and his brother-=
in-law is William Wright, an accounting officer at CEB Inc., which was acqu=
ired in 2017. The <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/=
26053246.265643/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9saXRpZ2F0aW9uL2xpdHJlbGVhc2VzLzI=
wMjAvbHIyNDk4Mi5odG0/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB96d7c73f" itemprop=3D"StoryLi=
nk" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text=
-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color=
: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">SEC sued la=
st December</a>. Last month, <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness=
.com/click/26053246.265643/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9saXRpZ2F0aW9uL2xpdHJl=
bGVhc2VzLzIwMjEvbHIyNTI2NC5odG0/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB17efc6f6" itemprop=
=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0=
00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
Wright settled</a>=C2=A0without admitting or denying the charges, agreeing =
to pay a fine of about $240,000 and to be barred from serving as a director=
 or officer of a public company for two years. But Clark went to trial, and=
 <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/26053246.265643/a=
HR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9hcnRpY2xlcy9zZWMtdGFrZXMtcmFyZS1jb3VydC1sb3NzLWlu=
LWluc2lkZXItdHJhZGluZy1jYXNlLTExNjM5NTE1ODY3P21vZD1pdHBfd3NqJnJ1PXlhaG9v/60=
7f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB526628bf" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemsc=
ope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !impo=
rtant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-botto=
m-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">this week he won</a>:</p><blockquo=
te><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A federal judge in northern Virginia on Mon=
day dismissed the civil fraud case against Christopher J. Clark, whose bull=
ish and risky trades just before a 2017 acquisition were spotted by regulat=
ors=E2=80=99 high-powered surveillance databases. The SEC alleged Mr. Clark=
=E2=80=99s brother-in-law, a former corporate accounting officer, told him =
days before the deal that Gartner Inc. would buy CEB Inc.</p><p style=3D"ma=
rgin: 16px 0;">U.S. District Judge Claude Hilton dismissed the SEC=E2=80=99=
s claims after regulators presented their evidence and before the case was =
sent to the jury. =E2=80=9CThere=E2=80=99s just simply no circumstantial ev=
idence here that gives rise to an inference that he received the insider in=
formation,=E2=80=9D Judge Hilton said Monday, according to a transcript. =
=E2=80=A6</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Mark Cummings, a lawyer for Mr. C=
lark, said the outcome underscores that regulators can rely too much on sta=
tistical evidence, such as trades made just before an event that caused a c=
ompany=E2=80=99s stock price to rise or fall. Data alone isn=E2=80=99t suff=
icient to support a civil or criminal case against a trader, he said.</p><p=
 style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Mr. Clark, 53 years old, refused to settle the S=
EC=E2=80=99s lawsuit because he had good reasons for believing CEB shares w=
ould rise, Mr. Cummings said. His research had nothing to do with his broth=
er-in-law, William Wright, who had worked as CEB=E2=80=99s corporate contro=
ller.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CThe lesson here is sus=
picious trading is not necessarily illegal trading,=E2=80=9D Mr. Cummings s=
aid. =E2=80=9CJust because the circumstances look bad, there can be an equa=
lly innocent reason for the activity.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=A6</p><p style=3D"mar=
gin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CThe government can speculate that he made a little t=
oo much money, he was a little too successful or more successful than he ou=
ght to be, so therefore he=E2=80=99s getting insider information,=E2=80=9D =
Judge Hilton said, according to the hearing transcript. =E2=80=9CBut there=
=E2=80=99s no evidence of it.=E2=80=9D</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: =
16px 0;">Notice that what happened here is=C2=A0<em>not=C2=A0</em>that the =
SEC presented all its suspicious evidence, Clark testified =E2=80=9Cno I di=
d my own research and it=E2=80=99s all innocent,=E2=80=9D and the=C2=A0jury=
 went and deliberated and decided that they believed him. Instead, what hap=
pened here is that the SEC presented all of its suspicious evidence and the=
 judge said =E2=80=9Cnope, there=E2=80=99s nothing here even worth botherin=
g a jury with.=E2=80=9D[2] Believing Clark=E2=80=99s explanation has nothin=
g to do with it; he didn=E2=80=99t even present his explanation. The judge =
just decided that the facts I laid out in my first paragraph=C2=A0=E2=80=94=
=C2=A0brothers-in-law, basketball games, mergers, short-dated out-of-the-mo=
ney call options =E2=80=94=C2=A0couldn=E2=80=99t possibly be=C2=A0enough, o=
n their own, to find someone liable for insider trading.=C2=A0</p><p style=
=3D"margin: 16px 0;">That will make life harder for the SEC! This is just o=
ne district judge=E2=80=99s decision in one case, and I would not exactly c=
all it The Law, and in any case nothing in this column is ever legal advice=
, but I will say, if you find yourself in the fact pattern in that first pa=
ragraph =E2=80=94=C2=A0if you have been trading short-dated out-of-the-mone=
y call options on a merger target after seeing your brother-in-law who is w=
orking on the merger =E2=80=94=C2=A0and the SEC comes after you for insider=
 trading, don=E2=80=99t give up hope. =E2=80=9CWhat, all of this is nothing=
,=E2=80=9D you can say to the SEC, and to a judge, and if nobody has any pr=
oof of what you talked about it might work.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"=
>Also I can=E2=80=99t believe Wright settled and has to pay the SEC $240,00=
0.=C2=A0<em>He=C2=A0</em>didn=E2=80=99t make that money trading call option=
s; Clark did, and Clark beat the charges. I know what Clark should give his=
 brother-in-law for Christmas this year.</p><table class=3D"liveintent-spon=
sored-content" width=3D"auto" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0">
